              "weight": 0,
              "type": "rich_text",
              "contents": {
                "singleSelect": true,
                "body": "<img src=\"https://static.remotasks.com/uploads/6892e922522126f1742d8678/1754549988927_m9qbuw.png\" alt=\"Slide title reads “Common Rubric Errors.”  The slide is arranged into six square tiles with alternating blue and purple backgrounds, each showing a common rubric issue:  Stacked (Non-Atomic) Criteria Criteria that check for multiple elements at once, making evaluation difficult.  Lacks Self-Containment Criteria depend on context instead of being evaluable on their own.  Implicit vs Explicit Confusion Not marking criteria as explicit when the prompt directly requires it.  Mislabeling Subjective vs. Objective Marking subjective criteria as objective when they rely on a feeling, emotion, or opinion.  Over-Prescriptive Imposing stylistic choices that aren't required by the prompt.  Criteria Overlap Different criteria check the same thing, which can lead to double-penalties.  Each tile includes a simple icon representing the error type.\">"
              },
              "_id": "689704a61db81d7051a20014"
            },
            {
              "id": "02561b7c-d859-473c-9e1c-69a994146a27",
              "weight": 0,
              "type": "rich_text",
              "contents": {
                "singleSelect": true,
                "body": "<img src=\"https://static.remotasks.com/uploads/6892e922522126f1742d8678/1754517013609_evuxsi.png\" alt=\"Slide title reads “Factually Wrong Information.” Subheading says: “Double-check all facts in prompts and criteria. Even if the source is provided by the user (e.g., a textbook or image), you are still responsible for ensuring the information is accurate and up to date.”  Two side-by-side boxes follow:  Left box (Expectation): Icon shows three sparkle lines. Text reads: “The contributor assumes the source text (like a textbook) is 100% accurate and uses it directly to write rubric items.”  Right box (Reality): Icon shows a lightning bolt. Text reads: “The textbook is outdated → Criteria based on it is now factually incorrect → Task fails when judged by current-day standards.”  Below these boxes is a light green box labeled Ideal Mindset, with a thought bubble icon. Text reads: “Are all of my criteria, prompts, and images factually correct based on current-day knowledge?”\">"
              },
              "_id": "689704a61db81d7051a20015"
            },
            {
